'''Cogital Group''' is a British multinational accounting and business services company.
Cogital Group is headquartered at 2 [[Babmaes Street]], [[St James's]], London SW1.<ref name="cogitalgroup.com">{{cite web|url=https://www.cogitalgroup.com/|title=Home - CogitalGroup|author=|date=17 May 2017|website=cogitalgroup.com|accessdate=26 January 2018}}</ref>
It was founded in August 2016 by [[John P. Connolly (businessman)|John Connolly]], the former senior partner and chief executive of [[Deloitte]] in the UK until his retirement in June 2011, with the financial backing of the private equity firm [[Hg (equity firm)|Hg Capital]].<ref name="auto">{{cite web|url=http://www.cityam.com/273157/city-grandee-john-connolly-reveals-cogitals-rapid-expansion|title=Big Four challenger Cogital has grown from zero to 4,600 staff in one year|first=Oliver|last=Gill|date=3 October 2017|website=cityam.com|accessdate=26 January 2018}}</ref><ref name="cogitalgroup.com"/>
