[[File:First-oil-well-in-bahrain.jpg|thumb|The '''first oil well''' in Bahrain was discovered in 1932]] [[File:Bahrain first oil well plaque.jpg|thumb|Plaque commemorating the discovery]] {{History of Bahrain}} As its name suggests, it is the '''first oil well''' in the Arabian side of the [[Persian Gulf]] and is located in [[Bahrain]]. The [[Oil well|well]] is situated below [[Mountain of Smoke|Jebel Dukhan]]. It was discovered and operated by [[Bahrain Petroleum Company|Bahrain Petroleum Company (BAPCO)]], established in 1929 in [[Canada]] by [[Standard Oil Company of California]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bBvz_YxlB-AC&pg=PA71|title=Historical dictionary of the petroleum industry|last=Vassiliou|first=Marius|publisher=[[Scarecrow Press]]|year=2009|isbn=9780810859937|series=Historical dictionaries of professions and industries|volume=3|location=|pages=71–72|author-link=Marius Vassiliou}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pNKfJ-cEXiMC&pg=PA146|title=Foreign Direct Investment in Bahrain|author=Lobna Ali Al-Khalifa|publisher=[[Universal-Publishers]]|year=2010|isbn=9781599423210|location=|page=146}}</ref>
[[Petroleum|Oil]] first spurted from this well on 16 October 1931, and the well finally began to blow heads of oil on the morning of 2 June 1932. The initial oil flow rate was {{convert|9600|oilbbl/d|m3/d}}; by the 1970s the well produced {{convert|70000|oilbbl/d|m3/d|abbr=on}}, and after that it stabilized at about {{convert|35000|oilbbl/d|m3/d|abbr=on}}.<ref>{{Cite book | last = | first = | authorlink = | title = The Report Bahrain 2009 | publisher = Oxford Business Group | year = 2009 | location = | page = 32 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=_MqUJPPPXwkC&pg=PT33 | doi = | id = | isbn = 978-1-907065-03-3}}</ref> In 1980, BAPCO was taken over by the Government of Bahrain<ref name=":0" />. Close to the well, which has been reconstructed to its first appearance, is a stable.<ref>{{Cite book | last = Walker | first = Jenny | authorlink = |author2=Stuart Butler |author3=Frances Linzee Gordon |author4=Terry Carter |author5=Lara Dunston | title = Oman, UAE & Arabian Peninsula | publisher = Lonely Planet | year = 2007 | location = | page = 134 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=nDsjyU2Re6AC&pg=PT134 | doi = | id = | isbn = 978-1-74104-546-8}}</ref>
Bahrain was the first place on the Arabian side of the [[Persian Gulf]] where oil was discovered, and it coincided with the collapse of the world [[pearl]] market.
